],\\\"S\\\":true}\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"11:T583,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Article\\\",\\\"@id\\\":\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/writing/interchange-iq-payment-fee-analyzer#article\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Interchange IQ: Building a Payment Fee Analyzer Around Real Processor Economics\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"See how Interchange IQ models payment processing costs across major processors using published interchange data, live fee comparison inputs, and breakeven analysis.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/writing/interchange-iq-payment-fee-analyzer\\\",\\\"datePublished\\\":\\\"2026-04-02\\\",\\\"dateModified\\\":\\\"2026-04-02\\\",\\\"inLanguage\\\":\\\"en-US\\\",\\\"isAccessibleForFree\\\":true,\\\"image\\\":[\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/og-image.png\\\"],\\\"author\\\":{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Person\\\",\\\"@id\\\":\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com#person\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Isaac Vazquez\\\",\\\"alternateName\\\":\\\"Isaac Vazquez\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Product Manager and UC Berkeley Haas MBA Candidate with 5+ years building SaaS products reaching 60M+ users. Case studies, product thinking, and PM frameworks.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com\\\",\\\"image\\\":\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/opengraph-image\\\",\\\"sameAs\\\":[\\\"https://linkedin.com/in/isaac-vazquez\\\",\\\"https://github.com/IsaacAVazquez\\\"],\\\"jobTitle\\\":\\\"Technical Product Manager \\u0026 UC Berkeley MBA Candidate\\\"},\\\"articleSection\\\":\\\"Payments\\\",\\\"wordCount\\\":992,\\\"keywords\\\":\\\"payment fee analyzer, interchange pricing, processor comparison tool, stripe vs square fees, payments economics, interchange plus pricing\\\"}\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"8:[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com#breadcrumb\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"itemListElement\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Home\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Writing\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/writing\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Interchange IQ: Building a Payment Fee Analyzer Around Real Processor Economics\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://isaacavazquez.com/writing/interchange-iq-payment-fee-analyzer\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"},\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$11\\\"},\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"min-h-screen py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"article\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"header\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mb-12\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Interchange IQ: Building a Payment Fee Analyzer Around Real Processor Economics\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-4 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 mb-6\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"time\\\",null,{\\\"dateTime\\\":\\\"2026-04-02\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"April 1, 2026\\\"}],[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"•\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"6 min read\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"•\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[992,\\\" words\\\"]}]]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Payments\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Payments\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Interchange\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Interchange\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Fintech Product\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Fintech Product\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Pricing\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Pricing\\\"}],\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"$L13\\\",\\\"$L14\\\"]}]]}],\\\"$L15\\\",\\\"$L16\\\"]}]}]]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"18:I[9148,[\\\"8500\\\",\\\"static/chunks/8500-41fa79ac743d83f1.js\\\",\\\"2159\\\",\\\"static/chunks/2159-a2185eb42de1551d.js\\\",\\\"8437\\\",\\\"static/chunks/8437-f676cf471bf9d370.js\\\",\\\"5851\\\",\\\"static/chunks/app/writing/%5Bslug%5D/page-7adc4d02f86dad9e.js\\\"],\\\"AuthorBio\\\"]\\n12:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Processor Economics\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Processor Economics\\\"}]\\n13:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Product Strategy\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Product Strategy\\\"}]\\n14:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Next.js\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 rounded-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Next.js\\\"}]\\n17:T1adf,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"\\u003ch1\\u003eInterchange IQ: Building a Payment Fee Analyzer Around Real Processor Economics\\u003c/h1\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eIf you want to use the tool first, open \\u003ca href=\\\"/fintech-tools/interchange-iq\\\"\\u003eInterchange IQ\\u003c/a\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eMost merchants know they are paying for card processing. Far fewer know what they are actually paying for.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThat confusion is not accidental. Processor pricing is full of blended rates, flat-rate convenience, card-mix variation, scheme complexity, and enterprise plans that only become legible once a business is already large enough to negotiate. For operators trying to make a clean decision, the market often feels deliberately hard to compare.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eI built Interchange IQ to make that comparison more concrete. The product is designed to answer a practical question: given your monthly volume, average ticket size, and card mix, how different do processor economics actually look?\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eThe Problem This Product Addresses\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eFor many businesses, processor choice is treated as a branding or convenience decision when it is really a margin decision.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe challenge is that the headline price rarely tells the whole story:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eflat-rate pricing is easy to understand, but it can hide meaningful overpayment at scale\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003einterchange-plus pricing can be cheaper, but it is harder to reason about without the underlying rate structure\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eticket size changes the impact of fixed per-transaction fees\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003edebit-heavy and Amex-heavy businesses do not behave the same way economically\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eA merchant does not need a theory lecture on payments. They need a model they can manipulate.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eWhy The Tool Starts With Published Interchange Data\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe core product decision was to make the calculator legible from first principles.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eInterchange IQ uses representative published interchange values and public processor pricing assumptions to show where the costs come from. That matters because a comparison tool is much more useful when the user can see the difference between:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003enetwork economics\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eprocessor markup\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003evolume sensitivity\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eticket-size sensitivity\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThis keeps the product grounded in real payments structure instead of turning it into a black-box recommendation engine.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe product does not try to predict every custom contract. It gives the user a way to understand the shape of the decision and the conditions that change it.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eThe Key Product Decisions\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003e1. Put Card Mix At The Center Of The Experience\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eCard mix is where processor comparisons start to become real.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eA business with a heavy debit profile behaves very differently from one with a premium credit and Amex-heavy mix. Showing only a headline rate would flatten that difference and make the tool less honest.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThat is why Interchange IQ lets the user adjust:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003emonthly processing volume\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eaverage transaction size\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ecredit-card share\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eAmex share within the credit mix\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThose inputs turn the product from a static comparison table into a working model.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003e2. Compare Flat Rate And Interchange+ On The Same Surface\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eMany payments explainers implicitly argue for one pricing model before showing the math. I wanted the product to do the opposite.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eInterchange IQ places flat-rate and interchange-plus options side by side so the user can see when simplicity is worth paying for and when it becomes too expensive. That is a better product experience than pushing a conclusion without exposing the tradeoff.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eIt also makes the tool useful across business maturity levels. A smaller operator may decide flat rate is still the right answer. A larger operator may realize the markup on interchange-plus becomes more compelling once volume rises or average ticket size increases.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003e3. Breakeven Analysis Matters More Than A Single Winner\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe cheapest option at one ticket size is not necessarily the cheapest option at another.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThat is why the tool includes breakeven logic. A single \\\"best processor\\\" label is too shallow. The better question is: at what point does the economic logic flip?\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eBreakeven analysis teaches the user how the market works, not just what the calculator currently outputs.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eHow The Experience Works\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe interface is intentionally direct:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003einputs define the business profile\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003esummary stats show the cheapest current option and monthly fee impact\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ea ranked comparison table surfaces effective rates and fee outcomes\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eexplanatory copy clarifies what card mix and pricing models actually mean\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThat structure is deliberate. Payments products can become abstract very quickly, so the interface needs to keep the user oriented around real operating questions:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ewhat happens if my volume doubles?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ewhat happens if my average ticket falls?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ehow much is flat-rate convenience costing me?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ewhen does interchange-plus start to win?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eTradeoffs I Chose On Purpose\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eEducation Over Exhaustiveness\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe tool covers major processors and representative rate assumptions. It does not try to model every private contract or every network nuance. That keeps the experience readable and useful for decision framing.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eTransparency Over Recommendation Theater\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eInterchange IQ shows the math drivers instead of dressing them up as a mysterious score. In payments, a product builds more trust when users can understand the model underneath it.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eProductized Explanation Over Dense Fintech Jargon\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe UI explains why debit, credit, and Amex matter because a calculator without explanation only helps people who already know the answer.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eWhat This Project Taught Me\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003ePayments is a strong product-design domain because so much of the value comes from making complexity legible.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe most important lesson here was that comparison products work best when they help users build intuition, not just produce outputs. The breakeven model, the card-mix controls, and the flat-rate versus interchange-plus framing all push in that direction.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eI also came away with a more durable belief about fintech products: users do not always need every edge case modeled. They need enough structure to see how the economics behave and enough clarity to make a better decision than they would have made with marketing pages alone.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch2\\u003eTry The Live Product\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eYou can run your own scenarios in \\u003ca href=\\\"/fintech-tools/interchange-iq\\\"\\u003eInterchange IQ\\u003c/a\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe fastest way to understand the product is to keep volume constant, then move average ticket size and card mix around. That exposes how quickly processor economics change once you stop treating the headline rate as the whole story.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"15:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-12\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$17\\\"}}]\\n16:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 mb-12\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L18\\\",null,{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"full\\\"}]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"d:[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"charSet\\\":\\\"utf-8\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"viewport\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\\\"}]]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"19:I[6869,[],\\\"IconMark\\\"]\\nb:null\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"f:[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"title\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Isaac Vazquez – Product Manager | UC Berkeley Haas MBA | Portfolio \\u